                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/1871: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-04T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 4, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 4—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>795. Information obtained by the United States Marines is to the effect that the
                    Japanese military and naval authorities here propose to take action, as
                    “neutrals”—but apparently as the forces in occupation of this part of China—to
                    notify the British and French forces here to withdraw whereupon the Japanese
                    would expect to take control of the administration of the French Concession and
                    International Settlement. The First Secretary of the Japanese Embassy during a
                    call on me this morning inquired whether I could confirm a report that the
                    United States Marines are to take over the British defense sector at Shanghai. I
                    replied that I had no information on the subject. He avoided any disclosure of
                    the Japanese attitude.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department only.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
